      <title>NOAA's annual winter forecast is here. These are the weather predictions for your area</title>
      <author>Juliana Kim</author>
      <link>https://www.npr.org/2024/10/18/nx-s1-5157206/noaa-winter-weather-outlook-2024-2025</link>
      <comments>https://text.npr.org/2024/10/18/nx-s1-5157206/noaa-winter-weather-outlook-2024-2025</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.npr.org/2024/10/18/nx-s1-5157206/noaa-winter-weather-outlook-2024-2025</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 18 Oct 2024 17:22:16 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div id="storytext" class="storytext storylocation linkLocation"&gt;       &lt;div id="resg-s1-28889" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 6558;         --source-height: 4372;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6558x4372+0+0/resize/1100/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F50%2Faa%2F4b6cfcff450e920e1cdd1d643528%2Fgettyimages-2076703127.jpg" class="img" type="image/webp" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6558x4372+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F50%2Faa%2F4b6cfcff450e920e1cdd1d643528%2Fgettyimages-2076703127.jpg" data-format="webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6558x4372+0+0/resize/1100/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F50%2Faa%2F4b6cfcff450e920e1cdd1d643528%2Fgettyimages-2076703127.jpg" class="img" type="image/jpeg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6558x4372+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F50%2Faa%2F4b6cfcff450e920e1cdd1d643528%2Fgettyimages-2076703127.jpg" data-format="jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6558x4372+0+0/resize/1100/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F50%2Faa%2F4b6cfcff450e920e1cdd1d643528%2Fgettyimages-2076703127.jpg" class="img" alt="A golden retriever races through the snow during a storm on March 14 in Boulder, Colorado." data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6558x4372+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F50%2Faa%2F4b6cfcff450e920e1cdd1d643528%2Fgettyimages-2076703127.jpg" data-format="jpeg" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 A golden retriever races through the snow during a storm on March 14 in Boulder, Colorado.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Mark Makela/Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Federal forecasters expect &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2021/10/15/1046313870/la-nina-winter-weather-us-temperatures-rainfall"&gt;a La Niña climate pattern&lt;/a&gt; to form in the coming months, according to a report released Thursday — offering a potential picture of what the weather could look like across the U.S. this winter.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;The &lt;a href="https://www.noaa.gov/news-release/us-winter-outlook-warmer-and-drier-south-wetter-north"&gt;annual winter outlook&lt;/a&gt; report from the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration's (NOAA) Climate Prediction Center details that a La Niña event has a 60% chance of emerging by the end of November. La Niña is characterized by cooler-than-normal ocean temperatures in the Pacific, which typically leads to drier and warmer conditions in the southern tier and cooler, wetter weather in the northern tier of the continental U.S. &lt;/p&gt;       &lt;div id="resnx-s1-5157206-100" class="bucketwrap internallink insettwocolumn inset2col"&gt;                     &lt;!-- END CLASS="BUCKET IMG" --&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;     &lt;!-- END ID="RESNX-S1-5157206-100" CLASS="BUCKETWRAP INTERNALLINK INSETTWOCOLUMN INSET2COL " --&gt;    &lt;p&gt;This year's La Niña is expected to be weaker and shorter in duration than ones in previous years, making it somewhat difficult to forecast months in advance.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;What federal forecasters do know so far is that large swaths of the South and the East Coast are favored to see warmer-than-average temperatures this winter. Its especially true for Texas and states along the Gulf Coast, like Alabama, Florida, Louisiana and Mississippi, according to NOAA.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-28909" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 3300;         --source-height: 2550;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3300x2550+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4c%2Fdc%2F250fa71b40cb87fe9f10d8ad18df%2Fgaghsq9xoaa4fvc.jpeg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3300x2550+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4c%2Fdc%2F250fa71b40cb87fe9f10d8ad18df%2Fgaghsq9xoaa4fvc.jpeg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3300x2550+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4c%2Fdc%2F250fa71b40cb87fe9f10d8ad18df%2Fgaghsq9xoaa4fvc.jpeg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3300x2550+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4c%2Fdc%2F250fa71b40cb87fe9f10d8ad18df%2Fgaghsq9xoaa4fvc.jpeg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3300x2550+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4c%2Fdc%2F250fa71b40cb87fe9f10d8ad18df%2Fgaghsq9xoaa4fvc.jpeg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3300x2550+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4c%2Fdc%2F250fa71b40cb87fe9f10d8ad18df%2Fgaghsq9xoaa4fvc.jpeg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3300x2550+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4c%2Fdc%2F250fa71b40cb87fe9f10d8ad18df%2Fgaghsq9xoaa4fvc.jpeg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3300x2550+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4c%2Fdc%2F250fa71b40cb87fe9f10d8ad18df%2Fgaghsq9xoaa4fvc.jpeg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3300x2550+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4c%2Fdc%2F250fa71b40cb87fe9f10d8ad18df%2Fgaghsq9xoaa4fvc.jpeg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3300x2550+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4c%2Fdc%2F250fa71b40cb87fe9f10d8ad18df%2Fgaghsq9xoaa4fvc.jpeg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3300x2550+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4c%2Fdc%2F250fa71b40cb87fe9f10d8ad18df%2Fgaghsq9xoaa4fvc.jpeg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3300x2550+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4c%2Fdc%2F250fa71b40cb87fe9f10d8ad18df%2Fgaghsq9xoaa4fvc.jpeg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3300x2550+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4c%2Fdc%2F250fa71b40cb87fe9f10d8ad18df%2Fgaghsq9xoaa4fvc.jpeg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3300x2550+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4c%2Fdc%2F250fa71b40cb87fe9f10d8ad18df%2Fgaghsq9xoaa4fvc.jpeg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3300x2550+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4c%2Fdc%2F250fa71b40cb87fe9f10d8ad18df%2Fgaghsq9xoaa4fvc.jpeg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3300x2550+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4c%2Fdc%2F250fa71b40cb87fe9f10d8ad18df%2Fgaghsq9xoaa4fvc.jpeg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3300x2550+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4c%2Fdc%2F250fa71b40cb87fe9f10d8ad18df%2Fgaghsq9xoaa4fvc.jpeg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3300x2550+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4c%2Fdc%2F250fa71b40cb87fe9f10d8ad18df%2Fgaghsq9xoaa4fvc.jpeg" class="img" alt="The 2024-2025 U.S. Winter Outlook map for temperature shows the greatest chances for cooler-than-average conditions will be in the Pacific Northwest of the U.S. " loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 The 2024-2025 U.S. Winter Outlook map for temperature shows the greatest chances for cooler-than-average conditions will be in the Pacific Northwest of the U.S.                  &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          NOAA                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Meanwhile, odds of cooler-than-normal conditions are higher for the Pacific Northwest to the northern High Plains. That includes states Washington, Oregon, Idaho, Montana, North Dakota, South Dakota, the western Minnesota, and northern Wyoming.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resnx-s1-5157206-101" class="bucketwrap internallink insettwocolumn inset2col"&gt;                     &lt;!-- END CLASS="BUCKET IMG" --&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;     &lt;!-- END ID="RESNX-S1-5157206-101" CLASS="BUCKETWRAP INTERNALLINK INSETTWOCOLUMN INSET2COL " --&gt;    &lt;p&gt;There is also a chance that the Pacific Northwest and parts of Montana and Wyoming will see wetter-than-average conditions in the coming months. Areas in the Great Lakes region are also at risk of a wetter-than-average conditions, with these probabilities being the strongest in portions of Ohio, Indiana and Kentucky.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Further south, there is a likelihood that states bordering the Gulf of Mexico, as well as Texas and southern New Mexico will experience drier-than-average conditions this winter.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resnx-s1-5157206-102" class="bucketwrap internallink insettwocolumn inset2col"&gt;                     &lt;!-- END CLASS="BUCKET IMG" --&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;     &lt;!-- END ID="RESNX-S1-5157206-102" CLASS="BUCKETWRAP INTERNALLINK INSETTWOCOLUMN INSET2COL " --&gt;    &lt;p&gt;NOAA also anticipates widespread moderate to extreme drought to persist across a majority of the Great Plains and portions of the Rocky mountains. Drought is also likely to develop or worsen across the Southwest and Gulf Coast. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Meanwhile, the center said drought conditions are expected to improve — or even possibly end — in parts of the Ohio River Valley, Great Lakes region and portions of the northwestern U.S. in Washington, Oregon and Idaho.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
